metadata.name: Cube Forest #23
metadata.description:
"Cube Forest" is the result of an algorithm that we have been working on for a long time. The first implementation of it was in the work entitled "Crystal Forest", below we leave the link in case you like to review it:
https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/27686

Over time this was improved, the current work has a depth detection system for the elements of the canvas. What results in obtaining a more natural image. It also has a unique filling algorithm, capable of coloring highly complex and personalized figures. In the same way, it allows you to recreate patterns within them. Recursive forms are used to reproduce the elements of nature such as trees and grass.

metadata.name: Vistas #79
metadata.description:
Vistas is an exploration in using layers to build an abstracted geometric landscape using a generative algorithm. But in a way that not only creates a digital image but also allows for the creation of an IRL physical artwork made from the 18 layers of laser cut wood. 

All mints created in first day will receive a free physical woodcut valued at ~$250. Up to 10% of all other mints may randomly get a free physical as well. 

Learn more about physicals: https://alleditions.art/p/vistas

The canvas for each output may be one of three different orientations, a square, portrait, or landscape. The portrait and landscape orientations create physicals that are 7.5 x 11.5 inches and square orientations create 7.5 x 7.5 inch physicals. 

The resulting output is carefully designed so that it can be exploded into discreet layers (Shift-E) and exported as an SVG (Shift-S) so it can be used to laser cut or plot an IRL physical artwork. 

A variety of elements are used to construct each unique one of a kind landscape. Sun, moon, sunbeams, stars, clouds, mountains, hills, plains, beaches, fields, water, boats, rocks, trees, and even mysterious obelisks. 



UTILITY

Shift - P to export a PNG
Shift - E explode the layers
Shift - S export a vector SVG

Slide the layers with the arrow keys. Click and drag the mouse to move the light source and adjust the layer shadows.

QUERY STRINGS

Add &screws=true to render with screw holes for cutting in order to assemble a physical with chicago screws.

Adjust the size of the output by adding &x=1150 and/or &y=1150 to adjust the physical size of the output where 100 = 1 inch.

metadata.name: Mandala #10
metadata.description:
A mandala is a geometric configuration of symbols.
With the help of vectors, the symmetrical geometric shapes of the mandala automatically attract the attention of the person to the center of the circle.
Most artists today draw mandalas without circles and squares, which is amazing from an aesthetic standpoint, but an original mandala with the characteristics that are present in the historical and ancient definitions will definitely have circles and squares.
Mandalas are seen by Carl Jung as archetypes of the self, symbols of wholeness and order, which are used to organize and rearrange chaos.
The mandala design is a way to relieve tension and focus the mind.
Mandalas are used in art therapy to help patients gain mastery over their minds and achieve peace, also Mandala establishes a new connection between the conscious and the unconscious.
This old pattern throws out internal issues and acts as a projection device.

Everyone in the world has their own mandala that can be formed in their paintings and artistic activities.

metadata.name: Silent Marsh #23
metadata.description:
Naturalism is the only art school faithful to nature among the visual arts. Including a descriptive painting of nature and minimally altered human figures.
The fidelity to nature gives the piece a photographic feel.
Like other painting schools, this style was heavily influenced by the (aesthetics) and (culture) of different regions.
Here, the only question is:
Is it possible for a painting to be completely naturalistic without the artist creating and reflecting his thoughts?

This collection represents our mental image of nature, which is implemented by code.

metadata.name: Less is More #41
metadata.description:
In this case, we tried to avoid abstract expressionist tendencies by removing personal scenarios.
Take a step back and let's create a geometrical work that intentionally avoids the usual conventional elements, focusing mainly on logic and physics concepts such as mathematical expansions and gravity.
In fact, we based our work and expression on the basis of simplicity and simple methods, as well as free from the usual philosophical or pseudo-philosophical complexity, and we concluded that by using simple geometric shapes, color, form, and material can be achieved in a pure manner.
